Paleoenvironment. Specimens from Windpassing and Pernersdorf (North Alpine Foreland Basin) derive from channels in which shallow marine faunas were transported into deeper habitats (e.g.
Zuschin et al . 2004
). The frequent occurrence and good preservation at Lăpugiu de Sus ( Romania ), in contrast, might indicate a preference for offshore environments in the middle to outer neritic.

Distribution.
Central Paratethys. Badenian (middle Miocene): 
North Alpine Foreland Basin
: Windpassing, Pernersdorf (
Austria
) (
Sieber 1960
; 
herein
); 
Carpathian Foreland Basin
: Jerutek at Lysice (
herein
), Korytnica (
Poland
) (
Bałuk 1975
); 
Eisenstadt-Sopron Basin
: Forchtenau (
Austria
) (
Sieber 1960
); 
Transylvanian Basin
: Lăpugiu de Sus (
Romania
) (
Zelei 2011
; 
herein
). A further occurrence might be documented by 
Hinculov (1968)
from the Badenian of Valea Sălişte in 
Romania
. The species seems to be restricted to the Langhian part of the Badenian stage; it is unknown so far from upper Badenian deposits.
